Description: An assay of genomic type (rnaseq, exomeseq, etc).
An assay of imaging type (ihc, etc).
Patient level metadata. Not for annotation.

Annotation template for simple endpoint data from clinical assays often used in diagnostic practice or clinical trials ; may include repeated measures and a treatment/intervention context. Examples include bloodwork results (creatine assay, serum antibody assay), tumor size measurements, or medication adherence. Note that clinical data are from human individuals, therefore species should be “human”.
A template that can be used for annotating scripts or source code for a software application.
Defines a metadata template for updating milestone report values in NF studies -- currently a supported feature for NTAP and GFF.
Parent attribute for the manifest template attributes.
